Tom Perez has been appointed as Senior Advisor, Assistant to the President, and Director of Intergovernmental Affairs. He will be succeeding Julie Chavez Rodriguez and will bring his extensive experience in local, state, and federal government to the role. Perez's background as a former county councilman, civil rights attorney, and Secretary of Labor will be beneficial in implementing the Invest in America agenda and ensuring that the government serves the people and communities effectively. The announcement was made by someone who has known Perez for years and looks forward to collaborating with him again.